Section 1:
1 L.D. 1318
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 JUDICIARY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 548, L.D. 1318, “An Act to Enhance
10 Data Collection Requirements Related to Immigration Status and Asylum Seekers to
11 Safeguard Services for Legal Residents”
12 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
13 following:
14 'Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §3110, sub-§3, ¶A, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 643, Pt. FF, §1, is
15 amended to read:
16 A. Collecting and analyzing relevant data, including but not limited to data regarding
17 the immigration status of individuals who receive publicly funded benefits in the State.
18 At a minimum and within existing resources, the Office of New Americans shall
19 contact all state and local government entities that provide services to immigrants in
20 the State and all nonprofit entities in the State that use local, state or federal funds to
21 provide services to immigrants in the State. The Office of New Americans shall request
22 that these entities provide aggregate data on the immigrants to whom they provide
23 publicly funded services, including data on the immigration status, county of residence,
24 employment status and vaccination status of the immigrants who receive publicly
25 funded services as well as a description of the types of services provided. Upon receipt
26 of the request, state government entities and nonprofit entities that use local, state or
27 federal funds shall provide the requested data. Local government entities may provide
28 any relevant data they collect in response to a request. The aggregate data submitted
29 to the Office of New Americans must preserve the anonymity of the immigrants who
30 receive publicly funded services and may not include information that refers to any
31 individual immigrant by name or number or in any other way that might lead to
32 identification of the individual;'
33 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
34 number to read consecutively.
Page 1 - 132LR2281(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 548, L.D. 1318
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, replaces the bill. The
33 amendment requires the Office of New Americans within the Office of Policy Innovation
44 and the Future, within existing resources, to collect and analyze data from state and local
55 government entities and from nonprofit agencies that provide publicly funded services to
66 immigrants in the State regarding the immigration status, county of residence, employment
77 status and vaccination status of the immigrants who receive publicly funded services as
88 well as a description of the types of services provided. The amendment requires state
99 government entities and nonprofit entities to provide the requested data and authorizes local
1100 government entities to provide the requested data. The data collected and analyzed by the
1111 Office of New Americans may not include any information that may be used to identify an
1122 individual recipient of publicly funded services.
1133 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1144 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR2281(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
