COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 548, L.D. 1318
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, replaces the bill. The
33 amendment requires the Office of New Americans within the Office of Policy Innovation
44 and the Future, within existing resources, to collect and analyze data from state and local
55 government entities and from nonprofit agencies that provide publicly funded services to
66 immigrants in the State regarding the immigration status, county of residence, employment
77 status and vaccination status of the immigrants who receive publicly funded services as
88 well as a description of the types of services provided. The amendment requires state
99 government entities and nonprofit entities to provide the requested data and authorizes local
1100 government entities to provide the requested data. The data collected and analyzed by the
1111 Office of New Americans may not include any information that may be used to identify an
1122 individual recipient of publicly funded services.
1133 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1144 (See attached)
